# Cloudflare MCP Server Authentication Configuration
# 
# This file stores authentication credentials for Cloudflare MCP servers.
# Create a user API token in the Cloudflare dashboard (https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens)
# with the appropriate permissions for each service you want to use.
#
# Required permissions by server:
#
# 1. Cloudflare Browser Rendering Server:
#    - Browser Rendering:Read
#
# 2. Cloudflare Workers Bindings Server:
#    - Workers:Read
#    - Workers KV Storage:Read
#    - Cloudflare Workers:Read (for R2 and Durable Objects)
#
# 3. Other servers (docs, radar) do not require authentication for basic access.
#
# SECURITY NOTE: Keep this file secure and never commit it to version control!

# Your Cloudflare User API Token
# Create at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your_api_token_here

# Account ID (optional, for some advanced features)
# Find at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your_account_id_here

# Example:
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef
